<a class="pn-title" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=article&amp;sid=40&amp;mode=thread&amp;order=0&amp;thold=0">You hear the pounding of hooves.</a><br/></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
<img src='themes//images/pixel.gif' height='5' width='1' border='0' alt=''/><br/>
</td></tr><tr><td class="article-table"><DIV ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://members.iinet.net.au/~freeth/eqscreens/lcupdates/181102/drunder.jpg" WIDTH="239" HEIGHT="15" ALT="" BORDER="0"></DIV><br />
<br />
We finally gained access to the Plane of Tactics recently, and immediately set to work exploring the zone. Quite possibly one of the nicest places we've seen so far in PoP, the whole zone looks very well designed and like it will be a lot of fun.. if you can avoid the stampeding boars. Our first target was Vallon Zek, a mean looking fellow and an encounter which we had a blast figuring out:<br />
<br />
<DIV ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://members.iinet.net.au/~freeth/eqscreens/lcupdates/181102/vallonzek.jpg" WIDTH="429" HEIGHT="642" ALT="" BORDER="0"></DIV><br />
<br />
We spent a couple of days on him with little luck, finally after much experimenting our late Sunday night crew of 46 cultists managed to push him over in a great show of teamwork.<br />
<br />
<DIV ALIGN="center"><A HREF="http://members.iinet.net.au/~freeth/eqscreens/lcupdates/181102/vallonzekcorpse.jpg"><IMG SRC="http://members.iinet.net.au/~freeth/eqscreens/lcupdates/181102/vallonzekcorpse_tn.jpg" WIDTH="400" HEIGHT="172" ALT="" BORDER="1"></A></DIV><br />
<br />
<DIV ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://members.iinet.net.au/~freeth/eqscreens/lcupdates/itempics/pendantofthetriumphantvictor.jpg" WIDTH="448" HEIGHT="237" ALT="" BORDER="0"><BR>Grats Kataisa and Batto!</DIV><br />
<br />
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH=50% ALIGN="center"><br />
<br />
Of course, in order to gain entry into Drunder, we had to kill off the Manaetic Behemoth in the Plane of Innovation. After having him warp on us at 50% last time, we headed back with a few alterations to the plan and proceeded to lay the smack down on this robotic contraption of war. We were rewarded with some pretty decent loots, and invited to follow the gnome on into the Fortress of Zek.<br />
<br />
<TABLE ALIGN="center" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=2><TR><TD ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://members.iinet.net.au/~freeth/eqscreens/lcupdates/itempics/protectivedustdrape.jpg" WIDTH="448" HEIGHT="237" ALT="" BORDER="0"><BR>Grats Xinae!</TD><TD ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://members.iinet.net.au/~freeth/eqscreens/lcupdates/itempics/selfcontainedforcebarrier.jpg" WIDTH="448" HEIGHT="237" ALT="" BORDER="0"><BR>Grats Shackmyn!</TD></TR></TABLE><br />
<br />
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH=50% ALIGN="center"><br />
<br />
In a busy few days for the cult, we also managed to take down Ryda'Dar in the Halls of Honor. Much like our first attempt at his relative in the Plane of Valor, this guy turned into something of a zerg-fest, however we emerged victorious with the first of our HoH trials completed.<br />
<br />
<DIV ALIGN="center"><IMG SRC="http://members.iinet.net.au/~freeth/eqscreens/lcupdates/181102/rydadarcorpse.jpg" ALT="" WIDTH="600" HEIGHT="318" BORDER="2"></DIV><br />
<br /><br /></td></tr></table><br/>
